1000 Most Asked “Why” Questions On Google

Have you ever wondered about finding out the most frequently asked “Why” questions on Google? Do you know the price advertisers around the globe are willing to pay for these terms? Well, worry not. We’re here to make things easier for you.

The entire list of top 1000 most asked popular “Why” questions on Google is given below for your reference.  Alongside you will also find the global search volume and cost-per-click (CPC) data. CPC or cost-per-click refers to the amount advertisers pay to advertise for that term on Google.

WHAT IS THE MOST ASKED “WHy” QUESTION IN THE WORLD?

Surprisingly, the most most commonly asked “why” question on Google is “why is there a leap day” with around 2 million searches. The 2nd place goes to the keyword – “why is the sky blue” with 135,000 searches. This is one compelling data that we found out in our research.

Similar to this, there are many more intriguing questions that show up in this list of the most searched “why” questions on Google.

The values under the ‘Global Search Volume’ column are monthly averages calculated using the data collected over the last 6 months. The entire list of “why” keywords has been generated using Mondovo’s Free Keyword Research Tool in just a few clicks and within seconds.
